The Chairman, Governing board, Nigerian Investment Promotion Commission (NIPC), Hon. Babangida Nguroje, has said that the synergy between the commission and the Federal Ministry of Special Duties and Inter-Governmental Affairs will see to the full optimization of the economic zones within the country and boost investments. He said this yesterday in Abuja during a courtesy visit on the Minister of Special Duties and Inter-Governmental Affairs, Senator George Akume. The NIPC board chairman reiterated the mandate of the commission, saying that the ministry will be a useful and profitable partner in the investment drive by the commission such that will boost the nation’s economy at all levels. Responding, the Minister of Special Duties and Inter-Governmental Affairs, Senator George Akume assured the NIPC chairman of his ministry’s desire to support and play a vital role in ensuring that the development agenda of the country is achieved. “The President has provided the way forward and we are going to follow it to the later to ensure that we create a future for our children and ones yet unborn,” Akume said. Wamakko chairs ACF’s 20th anniversary c’ttee Buhari to ministers: We must not fail 200m Nigerians Work for self-sufficiency, NIPC chairman urges youth Prostate  ENLARGEMENT? Don't Let Your PROSTATE Frustrate You! Here's A Better NATURAL Way To Shrink Your Prostate Enlargement! -No Surgery, -No Drugs. Shrink To Normal In Just 15 Days! Normalize Your Urination And Erection! Just Click To Get It Now!